    • GRAPH_ALISA_G

      static final String GRAPH_ALISA_G
      Represents the alias for the graph node in Cypher queries.

      In Cypher queries, aliases are used to assign temporary names to nodes or relationships, which can be referenced in subsequent parts of the query. Using aliases improves the readability and maintainability of the query, avoids ambiguity, and makes referencing easier.

      Example:

      MATCH (g:Graph { uuid: $graphUuid })-[:RELATION]->(n:GraphNode { uuid: $nodeUuid}) WITH g, n MATCH (n)-[relation:RELATION]-(m:GraphNode) RETURN m, relation In the above query, `g` is the alias for the graph node. The information of the graph node can be retrieved using `record.get(GRAPH_ALISA_G)`.

      See Also:
      • Constant Field Values
